data.meta_description: 26-jun-2024 - Alexander Troup (4 May 1895 – 1951), known as Alex Troup and Alec Troup, was a Scottish footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a winger. Troup played club football in Scotland and England for Dundee and Everton. Troup made five appearances for the Scotland national team between 1920 and 1926. 1923–1930 Everton	260 League Appearances 35 Goals.
